As for the problem with OpenEditorCommand not bringing up the skeleton file, you should change the Axis2SkelImplCommand to something like the following:

		try {
			String serviceSkeletonImplURLString =  serviceSkeletonImplURLPath.toFile().toURL().toString();
			webServiceInfo.setImplURL(serviceSkeletonImplURLString);
			String[] implURLArray = {serviceSkeletonImplURLString};
			webServiceInfo.setImplURLs( implURLArray);

		} 

I tested it out and the Java Editor is bringing up the skeleton file no problem with this change.  Please note that multiple skeleton file could be generated, so the code would need to set the skeleton impl URL accordingly (this could be handled later on as a defect).  The current code assumes that only 1 skeleton file would be generated.
